# üîç Ledger vs GL vs Trial Balance (Clear Comparison)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| ‡¶¨‡¶ø‡¶∑‡ßü          | Ledger (Sub-Ledger)       | GL                  | Trial Balance  |
| ------------- | ------------------------- | ------------------- | -------------- |
| Level         | Detail (Customer-wise)    | Summary (Head-wise) | Summary Check  |
| Purpose       | Daily ops, SMS, Statement | Financial records   | Accuracy check |
| Customer Name | ‡¶•‡¶æ‡¶ï‡ßá                      | ‡¶•‡¶æ‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶®‡¶æ             | ‡¶•‡¶æ‡¶ï‡ßá ‡¶®‡¶æ        |
| Output        | Balance per account       | Total per head      | Debit = Credit |
| CBS Role      | Operational               | Official book       | Validation     |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

---

# üß† ‡¶Æ‡¶®‡ßá ‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶ñ‡¶æ‡¶∞ ‡¶∏‡¶π‡¶ú ‡¶≤‡¶æ‡¶á‡¶®

> Ledger = ‡¶ó‡ßç‡¶∞‡¶æ‡¶π‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶ñ‡¶æ‡¶§‡¶æ
> GL = ‡¶¨‡ßç‡¶Ø‡¶æ‡¶Ç‡¶ï‡ßá‡¶∞ ‡¶ñ‡¶æ‡¶§‡¶æ
> Trial Balance = ‡¶π‡¶ø‡¶∏‡¶æ‡¶¨ ‡¶Æ‡¶ø‡¶≤‡¶æ‡¶®‡ßã‡¶∞ ‡¶§‡¶æ‡¶≤‡¶ø‡¶ï‡¶æ

---

## üéØ Interview / Exam One-Liners

- Ledger records detailed transactions for a specific account.
- General Ledger summarizes all ledgers for reporting.
- Trial Balance checks whether debits equal credits.

